reviewText: Great product for a great price.

The 3rd movie, "Clash Of The Titans", that was included in the case was the original 1968 version instead of the newer version with Liam Neeson. Don't get me wrong, I like the older version as well, but that was not what I was expecting.

These 4 movies are filled with drama, and action. For a movie night, they keep you entertained from start to finish. 'The Haunting' grabs your attention & keeps it until the end with suspense, and unexpected twists-and-turns. The Price for the 4 Films is much less expensive, then when I paid double to see One movie on release day, that became a total disappointment. At least, we can add this to our collection & watch it on movie nights, by picking & choosing to our preferences. Entertaining & Good Price. Highly recommended!

Actor Liam Neeson is great in everything he does ,especially in action flicks .Have not seen K-19 but the Haunting was good

with impressive special effects and good cast,Original Clash of the Titans lacks the special effects the remake has ,but still good

film to watch. i would still recommend it!
The Clash of the Titans (Which is supposed to be the 2010 version with Liam Neeson) is not in fact the 2010 one with Liam Neeson. It's the original 1981 movie. The other movies are good though.

K-19: The Widowmaker, The Haunting, Clash Of The Titans, Unknown
Wish it had some of his better movies like Rob Roy, Les Miserables & Taken.
This is a good set at a good price.

I guess I didn't read the reviews far enough back....this is supposed to be a Liam Neeson favorites but I got the original Clash of the Titans as well....not what was advertised.  The other movies are fine, arrived in a timely fashion and in good condition
